FBIS4-51315 "drchi103_g_94004" FBIS-CHI-94-103 Daily Report 20 May 1994 Sub-Saharan Africa CPC's Li Tieying Meets Seychelles Guests CPC's Li Tieying Meets Seychelles Guests OW2005082094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0758 GMT 20 May 94 OW2005082094 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, May 20 (XINHUA) -- Li Tieying, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), met here today with a delegation from the Seychelles People's Progressive Front (SPPF). Li briefed the delegation, which is headed by its Deputy General Secretary James Alix Michel, on the development of China's socialist market economy and the restructuring of its economic system. He noted that China has decided to build a socialist market economy with Chinese characteristics on the basis of its experience gained in past years of reform and opening-up and by drawing on experiences of other countries. Li, also Chinese minister in charge of the State Commission for Restructuring the Economy, said that the restructuring of China's economic system is focused on establishment of the modern enterprises system. Li asked Michel to convey greetings from Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng to President France Albert Rene of Seychelles. Michel, also minister of defense and finance of Seychelles, said great changes have taken place in China since his last trip to the country ten years ago. He voiced the hope that relations between his country and China, especially in the field of economy and trade, will be further enhanced. The SPPF delegation arrived here on may 16 as guests of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee.
